               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18370403-name-628" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18370403-name-628" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18370403-name-628" type="surname" value="JONES"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18370403-name-628" type="given" value="THOMAS PRYCE"></interp>THOMAS PRYCE JONES</persName>
                  </hi>. I live in Tothill-street, Westminster. I saw these four handkerchiefs hanging inside my shop, on the 18th of March, about half-past eleven o'clock at night—between that and twelve o'clock the policeman came in, and asked if I had lost any thing—I said "very likely, "as I had seen a man run very quickly out of the shop—I described his dress to the policeman—he had a jacket, a white apron, and a cap on—these four handkerchiefs are mine—they have my tickets on the corner.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner. Q.</hi> Did you see me in the shop? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> Yes, you had been in the shop, and brought a duplicate to me—I said it did not belong to us.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18370403-name-629" type="witnessName">
